Common expressions that can increase results: Masterpiece, trend on artstation, trend on pixiv, vivid, dynamic, geometric, intricate, high quality, detailed. From discord NightCafe Server: For me I've always used quotes to show the ai what my promot is when it comes to generalist models as the one NC is using exclamation marks are generally doin the same thing and giving importance to the prompt same thing goes for question marks although this was just a myth back in the day. Although I will say doing so adds spice or a random seasoning to a dish. As for :: it's a replacement for commas for more prompt room, it works as a divider of prompts the same way commas w ould but without using the character count so it was really useful for single prompts. However nowadays instead of using quotations I use "(red eyes:1.2)" since various other generators recognize this method more often than not. Note that the numbers stand for the prompt weight and the parentheses seperate the subjects so whatever was inside would be what the 1.2 would effect you can use various weights but anything from 0.5 to 1.2 or 1.3 is best above that and it'll get overcooked and lose its meaning
